basics.name: Sergeant E-5 Aviation Supply Specialist
basics.label: Supply Specialist
basics.summary: A highly motivated and ambitious individual able to give timely and accurate advice, guidance, and support to team members and individuals. Possess excellent management skills and have the ability to work with the minimum of supervision whilst supporting fellow team members. Have a proven ability to lead by example, consistently hit targets, improve best practices and organize time efficiently.

work.name: Company Name
work.position: Order, Track, Receive, and Distribute Organizational Level Maintenance Material
work.summary: Responsible for inventory control, planning inventory management techniques to avoid shortages and excesses. Led the Tool Control Program and Respirator Program, maintained records for maintenance and installation, and handled weekly payroll for up to 20 crew workers.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Supervised, trained and evaluated personnel Marines to most proficiently support over 10 Marine Aircraft Squadrons and 15 Intermediate Maintenance Activities.

work.name: Company Name
work.position: FEMALE ENGAGEMENT TEAM LIAISON/ PLATOON LEADER
work.summary: Successfully completed a 5 month, Pre-Afghanistan deployment training including, among others, Casualty Assessment, Immediate Action Drills, Combat Lifesaving, and Cross Cultural Engagement Training that helped to successfully complete a tour in Musa Qal'eh.

awards.title: Navy and Marine Corps Achievement Medal
awards.summary: Received while serving as squad leader, 2nd Platoon, Female Engagement Team, 2nd Marine Division (Forward) for having coordinated three Female Engagement teams and led over 85 missions, engaged more than 1900 local nationals during 1300 engagements while serving in direct support of 3rd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment from March 2011 to October 2011.

awards.title: Certificate of Commendation
awards.summary: Received while serving as Expeditionary Airfields Supply Warehouse Clerk during the Commanding Generals Inspection for superior leadership, organizational skills and managerial abilities.
